<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-04-16T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-04-16T03:00:00-05:00" n="668" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d668">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/13019: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Cunningham</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-04-16T16:00:00+08:00">April 16, 1935—4
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received April 16—8:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I am informed by British Consul General that he understands that as a
                            precautionary measure the foreign women and children are being evacuated
                            from Chengtu owing to the danger from communistic attack. Repeat[ed to]
                            the Hankow Consulate General. Repeated to the Department.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cunningham</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>